-- descriptions-update-9.sql
-- Plain prose descriptions for 10 batch-16 tools
-- No em dashes. Two paragraphs per tool. 150-250 words each.

UPDATE tools SET description = 'Wordware is an AI application builder that lets non-engineers create and deploy sophisticated AI workflows using a document-like interface. Instead of writing code, you describe the logic you want in plain language, define inputs and outputs, and Wordware compiles it into a working AI application. Teams use it to build internal tools, customer-facing chatbots, document processors, and automated workflows without touching infrastructure. The built-in prompt editor lets you iterate on AI behavior in real time, and version control tracks changes across your team.

What separates Wordware from general no-code tools is its focus on AI-native workflows rather than adapting traditional automation logic to AI tasks. It connects natively to OpenAI, Anthropic, and Mistral models, and supports RAG pipelines, tool calling, and multi-step agent behavior. For product and ops teams who want to build with AI but cannot allocate engineering resources, Wordware reduces the gap between what is possible and what is buildable.' WHERE slug = 'wordware';

UPDATE tools SET description = 'Cline is an open-source AI coding assistant that runs directly inside Visual Studio Code as an extension. Unlike cloud-based tools that send your code to remote servers, Cline operates with full access to your local file system, terminal, and browser - giving it the ability to read project context, run commands, browse documentation, and make multi-file edits autonomously. The agentic approach means you can describe a task at a high level and Cline handles the execution, asking for confirmation before making destructive changes.

Cline supports any OpenAI-compatible API, including local models run through Ollama or LM Studio, which makes it practical for teams with data privacy requirements who cannot use cloud-based AI tools. Its transparent approval model - every file change and terminal command is shown before execution - gives developers confidence that the AI is doing what they expect. For developers who want deep IDE integration without locking into a proprietary tool, Cline is one of the strongest open-source options available.' WHERE slug = 'cline';

UPDATE tools SET description = 'Firecrawl is an API-first web scraping and crawling service designed specifically for feeding clean data to AI applications. Given a URL, Firecrawl crawls an entire website, extracts the readable content, and returns it as clean markdown suitable for LLM ingestion. It handles JavaScript-rendered pages, respects robots.txt, manages rate limiting automatically, and can be configured to scrape specific elements using CSS selectors or natural language descriptions of what you want to extract.

The tool is built for developers building RAG pipelines, competitive intelligence tools, research assistants, and any AI application that needs fresh web data as context. Instead of writing custom scrapers that break every time a site updates its layout, teams use Firecrawl as a reliable data pipeline. It integrates with LangChain, LlamaIndex, and the major vector database providers. The API is straightforward, pricing is usage-based, and a free tier covers small projects and prototyping.' WHERE slug = 'firecrawl';

UPDATE tools SET description = 'Hailuo AI is a video generation model developed by MiniMax that produces high-quality short video clips from text prompts or reference images. It is known for its cinematic visual quality, natural motion, and strong prompt adherence - benchmarks where it competes directly with Runway and Kling. Hailuo is particularly strong at generating realistic human movement and facial expressions, which makes it a popular choice for character-driven video content, product visualizations, and marketing material.

The model became widely known after viral social media videos demonstrated its ability to generate convincing human performances from simple text descriptions. Access is available through the MiniMax API and through several third-party platforms that have integrated the model. For video creators and marketing teams looking to add AI-generated footage to their workflows, Hailuo offers a quality tier that previously required significantly more expensive tooling.' WHERE slug = 'hailuo';

UPDATE tools SET description = 'Veo is Google DeepMind''s video generation model, capable of producing high-definition video clips up to one minute in length from text or image prompts. It was trained on a large dataset of professional video content and supports a wide range of cinematic styles - from documentary realism to stylized animation. Veo understands complex prompts involving camera movement, depth of field, lighting conditions, and scene continuity, making it one of the most controllable text-to-video models available to creators.

Access to Veo is available through Google''s VideoFX and through the Gemini API for developers. It is positioned as a professional creative tool rather than a consumer product, with an emphasis on quality over speed. For filmmakers, advertising agencies, and video production studios experimenting with AI-assisted production, Veo represents Google''s most serious entry into the generative video space. Its integration with the broader Google ecosystem means it will likely appear in products like YouTube Studio and Google Workspace in the near future.' WHERE slug = 'veo';

UPDATE tools SET description = 'Flux is an image generation model developed by Black Forest Labs, the team behind the original Stable Diffusion research. The Flux model family - Flux.1 Dev, Flux.1 Schnell, and Flux.1 Pro - covers a range from fast open-source generation to high-quality commercial output. Flux is known for exceptional typography handling, which has long been a weakness of diffusion models, as well as improved anatomical accuracy and photorealistic rendering of human subjects.

The open weights release of Flux.1 Dev made it immediately popular in the creative and developer community, leading to rapid adoption across image generation platforms including ComfyUI, Replicate, and fal.ai. For artists, designers, and developers who run their own image generation workflows, Flux provides a significant quality upgrade over earlier open models without the restrictions of proprietary alternatives. Commercial users can access the Pro tier through the Black Forest Labs API with pricing based on per-image generation.' WHERE slug = 'flux';

UPDATE tools SET description = 'Adobe Lightroom AI encompasses the machine learning-powered tools built into Adobe Lightroom Classic and Lightroom CC for automated photo editing, organization, and enhancement. The AI features cover the full editing workflow: AI-powered Masking selects subjects, skies, and backgrounds automatically for targeted adjustments; Denoise removes grain from high-ISO shots while preserving fine detail; Enhance Detail increases effective resolution; and the Generative Remove tool eliminates unwanted objects and fills in the background seamlessly.

For photographers who process large volumes of images - wedding photographers, event photographers, commercial studios - the AI tools in Lightroom dramatically reduce editing time. A batch of 500 wedding photos that previously required hours of manual culling and correction can be processed with consistent edits applied automatically across similar shots. Adobe Lightroom is available as part of the Creative Cloud Photography plan starting at around $9.99 per month, or as a standalone Lightroom subscription at a similar price.' WHERE slug = 'adobe-lightroom-ai';

UPDATE tools SET description = 'Shorts AI is an automated short-form video creation platform that repurposes long-form video content into clips optimized for YouTube Shorts, TikTok, Instagram Reels, and similar platforms. It analyzes the source video, identifies the most engaging moments based on speech patterns, on-screen activity, and audio energy, and generates clips with automatic captions, aspect ratio conversion, and B-roll suggestions. The goal is to turn a one-hour podcast, webinar, or interview into ten shareable clips with minimal manual editing.

The platform is designed for content teams and individual creators who want to maximize the reach of existing video content without spending hours in an editing timeline. It competes directly with Opus Clip and Submagic in a growing category of AI repurposing tools. Shorts AI differentiates on its caption styling options and the precision of its moment-detection algorithm, which reduces the number of clips that miss the context needed to stand alone. Plans are subscription-based with pricing determined by the volume of source video processed per month.' WHERE slug = 'shorts-ai';

UPDATE tools SET description = 'Venice AI is a privacy-focused AI platform that runs inference locally or in isolated cloud environments, ensuring that your conversations, images, and documents are never used to train models or accessed by third parties. It provides access to leading open-source models including Llama, Mistral, and Flux image generation through a clean interface, and positions itself as the privacy-preserving alternative to ChatGPT and Claude for users who handle sensitive professional or personal information.

The platform appeals to legal professionals, healthcare workers, journalists, and enterprise teams who need the capability of frontier AI models without the data retention policies of mainstream AI providers. Venice AI charges a subscription fee rather than selling advertising or monetizing usage data, which aligns its business model with user privacy rather than against it. For individuals and organizations where data confidentiality is a hard requirement, Venice AI provides a credible path to using powerful AI tools without compromising sensitive information.' WHERE slug = 'venice-ai';

UPDATE tools SET description = 'Trae is an AI-powered code editor developed by ByteDance, positioning itself as a free alternative to Cursor and Windsurf with deep integration of multiple AI models including Claude, GPT-4, and ByteDance''s own models. It offers an agent mode for autonomous multi-step coding tasks, inline code completion, chat-based code editing, and a builder mode for generating entire project scaffolds from natural language descriptions. The editor is built on the VS Code codebase, which means it supports existing VS Code extensions and is familiar to a large existing user base.

Trae''s primary differentiator is its pricing: the base version is free with generous usage limits, making it accessible to students, independent developers, and teams that find Cursor''s subscription pricing prohibitive. ByteDance''s backing gives it the infrastructure to sustain a free tier at scale while continuing to develop the model integrations. For developers who want an AI-native editor without a monthly subscription, Trae is worth evaluating alongside Codeium and GitHub Copilot as a zero-cost starting point.' WHERE slug = 'trae';
